\begin{frame}{Hypothesis: warm-rain fraction can serve as an observational constraint on
    the cloud lifetime effect}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Aerosol influence mainly acts on autoconversion in liquid-water
    clouds in current models
    \vfill
  \item The more precipitating warm clouds are simulated in a model, the more
    opportunity aerosols have to influence the precipitation microphysics
    \vfill
  \item We hypothesize that the strength of the cloud lifetime effect in models
    is therefore related to the warm-rain fraction
    \vfill
  \item This hypothesis can be tested in GCMs with parameterized cloud
    lifetime effect
    \vfill
  \item Comparing warm-rain fraction in models against satellites may provide an
    observational constraint on the cloud lifetime effect
  \end{itemize}
\end{frame}

