\begin{frame}{Tuning the warm rain fraction in ECHAM--HAM: conclusions}
  \begin{itemize}
  \item Satellite warm-rain fraction can be reproduced in ECHAM--HAM by
    multiplying the Khairoutdinov and Kogan (2000) autoconversion rate by
    $10^{-4}$\\ (default ECHAM--HAM tuning factor: 4)
    \vfill
  \item Alternative to this drastic scale factor: $r_e > 17\mu$m threshold on
    autoconversion 
    \vfill
  \item Effect on radiative balance is large (large increase in cloud lifetime)
    \vfill
  \item Reducing the warm-rain fraction to match the satellite climatology also
    increases the intensity spectrum 
    \vfill
  \item (Some remaining uncertainty on these numbers because of parameter
    choices in diagnosis of warm-rain fraction)
  \end{itemize}
  
\end{frame}

